com.cyc.baseclient.cycobject

Class CycArrayList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • java.util.ArrayList<E>
          • com.cyc.baseclient.cycobject.CycArrayList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CycList<E>, CycObject, Serializable, Cloneable, Comparable<Object>, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, List<E>, RandomAccess
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CycArrayList.UnmodifiableCycList

    public class CycArrayList<E>
extends ArrayList<E>
implements CycList<E>, CycObject
    Provides the behavior and attributes of a Base Client list, typically used to represent assertions in their external (EL) form.
    Version:
    $0.1$
    Author:
    Stephen L. Reed
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • construct

        @Deprecated
public static <T> CycList<T> construct(T object1,
                                                   Object object2)
        Deprecated. 
        Constructs a CycArrayList using the semantics of Lisp symbolic expressions.
        1. construct(a, NIL) --> (a)
        2. construct(a, b) --> (a . b)

        Deprecated: Use addToBeginning(E) or makeDottedPair(T,T) instead.

        Parameters:
        object1 - the first Object in the CycArrayList
        object2 - NIL or an Object
        Returns:
        CycArrayList (object) if object2 is NIL, otherwise return the improper CycArrayList (object1 . object2)
